1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,210
Why are you wearing that?

2
00:00:02,293 --> 00:00:06,172
Jalil Abubakar's transfer
was assigned to me.

3
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:08,508
- [Usman] <i>Buddy, they will kill Jalil.</i>
- What?

4
00:00:09,551 --> 00:00:10,677
- What happened?
- [coughs]

5
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:12,053
- [overlapping chatter]
- [Montes] Hey!

6
00:00:12,637 --> 00:00:14,389
[groans] Argh!

7
00:00:14,472 --> 00:00:15,640
[Jalil] What's going on?

8
00:00:15,724 --> 00:00:17,017
We need to leave,
or else they'll kill you.

9
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:18,893
[Jalil] <i>Thank you for saving me.</i>

10
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:19,936
[Usman] Use this.

11
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,229
What about you?

12
00:00:21,312 --> 00:00:23,523
What's important is that you're safe.
I can handle myself.

13
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:25,233
[Montes] <i>Sabdani, you bastard!</i>

14
00:00:25,316 --> 00:00:26,901
<i>You let that criminals escape!</i>

15
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:29,112
- What are you doing?
- What? Huh?

16
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:31,406
- Try touching him, I dare you!
- Go ahead!

17
00:00:31,489 --> 00:00:33,408
- What's going on here?
- [fire alarm blaring]

18
00:00:33,491 --> 00:00:36,745
[in English] Sabdani,
you are hereby suspended

19
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,580
pending further investigation.

20
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:42,751
[Usman] <i>I will never regret defending</i>
<i>my Muslim brother</i>

21
00:00:42,834 --> 00:00:44,210
<i>from this rotten system.</i>

22
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:46,337
[Marcus] <i>Thank you</i>
<i>for what you did for Jalil.</i>

23
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:47,839
I know I did the right thing.

24
00:00:47,922 --> 00:00:49,048
Jalil

25
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:50,550
is Gabriel.

26
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,761
<i>I will put an end to Carillo's plans.</i>

27
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:55,764
I'll seek justice for the death
of my Father,

28
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:56,723
Lara,

29
00:00:57,265 --> 00:00:59,392
- my fellow villagers on the island,
- [gunshots blasting]

30
00:00:59,476 --> 00:01:02,645
and even the innocent lives
that he destroyed.

31
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:04,522
I will find that bastard.

32
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:06,900
[Marcus] <i>Tell me where you are, Gabriel,</i>

33
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:08,318
- <i>so I can protect you.</i>
- [rapid gunfire]

34
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:11,404
[Jamilah] <i>I'm thinking about the places</i>
<i>Jalil could hide.</i>

35
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:15,575
<i>He could be at the safe house</i>
<i>where Sir Mustapha hid Father.</i>

36
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:19,746
[Carillo, in English]
Marcus Reyes and Jalil Abubakar

37
00:01:19,829 --> 00:01:22,165
are enemies of the State.

38
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:25,251
[in English] <i>And they</i>
<i>must be neutralized on sight.</i>

39
00:01:25,835 --> 00:01:27,212
[Felix] Both of them are the criminals,

40
00:01:27,295 --> 00:01:29,422
yet you are accusing me?

41
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:30,465
How dare you!

42
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:33,051
- You're all acting so brave!
- You're really stupid, Domingo

43
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:35,845
[Marcus] <i>We'll bring down</i>
<i>General Carillo together.</i>

44
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:37,388
<i>We are allies and brothers.</i>

45
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:39,140
[Marcus] The fight
just became more difficult,

46
00:01:39,224 --> 00:01:42,310
but in the end,
we will still bring them down.

47
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:52,153
[mysterious theme music playing]

48
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:04,541
[in English] Keep your guards up!

49
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:06,626
Carillo will seize this opportunity

50
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:09,462
to get rid of everyone who's against him.

51
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,674
[Ryan] Sir, does that mean
he'll get rid of us too?

52
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:13,633
Who else do you think?

53
00:02:13,716 --> 00:02:15,510
[pensive music playing]

54
00:02:15,593 --> 00:02:17,220
The people on his side…

55
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:20,056
they'll what?
Act high and mighty around here?

56
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:23,351
That's why you should all be prepared.

57
00:02:24,352 --> 00:02:25,645
War has already begun.

58
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:28,523
[tense music playing]

59
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:43,163
[dramatic sting]

60
00:02:43,746 --> 00:02:45,165
[in English] Goddammit.

61
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:47,834
Bro.

62
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:49,502
[gentle music playing]

63
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:50,753
[whispers, in English] You're alive.

64
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:53,715
What happened to you? [sniffles]

65
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:57,176
- Huh?
- My memories are back, sir.

66
00:02:58,219 --> 00:02:59,470
You're alive. [sniffles]

67
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:02,849
[Harold] Sir.

68
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,643
I can come back to work.

69
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:09,147
[melancholic music playing]

70
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,773
[Azuelo, in English] Welcome back, Rustia.

71
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:14,277
[foreboding music playing]

72
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:17,488
Marcus, how are you and Gabriel?

73
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,491
Ma, Gabriel and I are safe.

74
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:23,912
Jamilah, don't worry.

75
00:03:23,995 --> 00:03:25,663
I'm with Marcus.

76
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:27,999
Jalil, be careful.

77
00:03:28,082 --> 00:03:32,128
Ma, you need to watch your back
and find somewhere to hide.

78
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,172
[Marcus] <i>You'll definitely be targeted</i>

79
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:36,216
<i>by the people who see me</i>
<i>and Gabriel as enemies.</i>

80
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:39,010
They could strike back
and use you against us.

81
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:40,887
My goodness.

82
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:44,349
[suspenseful music playing]

83
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:45,683
Mama…

84
00:03:48,686 --> 00:03:50,313
Mama, expect Usman any minute now.

85
00:03:51,105 --> 00:03:52,482
He'll come to pick you up.

86
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:54,984
Gabriel… My son.

87
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:59,906
[sniffles] I've dreamed of the day
the three of us would be reunited.

88
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:03,701
But… [sniffles] I never thought
it would happen this way.

89
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:05,328
I know, Mama.

90
00:04:05,411 --> 00:04:06,704
[morose music playing]

91
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:08,289
Don't worry.

92
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,625
We'll be reunited soon.
All of this will be resolved.

93
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:12,627
We won't give up.

94
00:04:13,628 --> 00:04:16,297
Be careful, my boys, won't you? [sniffles]

95
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:17,757
Marcus.

96
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,509
Gabriel.

97
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:22,428
[sniffles] I love you both so much.

98
00:04:22,512 --> 00:04:25,306
[morose music continues]

99
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,474
Uh…

100
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,605
Yes, Mama. Bye.

101
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,483
Take care of yourselves, Ma.

102
00:04:35,566 --> 00:04:37,277
[Teresa crying softly]

103
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:40,113
[smooches, crying softly]

104
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:44,117
[sighs]

105
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:49,831
[inhales deeply]

106
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:54,419
- [unsettling music playing]
- [door clicks shut]

107
00:04:57,755 --> 00:04:59,132
Rustia!

108
00:05:01,676 --> 00:05:02,552
Felix.

109
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:04,762
Were you asked to report
to the Task Force Alpha?

110
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:06,139
I'm not cleared yet.

111
00:05:07,056 --> 00:05:10,351
I'm still recovering,
so I'm limited to light duty.

112
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:12,437
Crazy, right?

113
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:14,897
So much has changed here.

114
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:18,860
It was a shock to me,

115
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:24,240
finding out that Oliver,
Patrick, and Russel are dead.

116
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:27,201
Right.

117
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:28,244
[clears throat]

118
00:05:29,871 --> 00:05:31,164
It's infuriating, isn't it?

119
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:35,877
In fact, we thought you were
among the casualties

120
00:05:36,627 --> 00:05:37,962
from the incident on the island.

121
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,839
Fortunately, that's not the case.

122
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:42,508
I was badly hurt.

123
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:45,136
But here I am, still alive and kicking.

124
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:48,139
The waters carried me
to a neighboring island.

125
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:52,769
Luckily, there were good people
there who took care of me.

126
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:55,772
When I regained consciousness,

127
00:05:57,315 --> 00:05:58,900
I couldn't remember anything.

128
00:06:00,109 --> 00:06:02,111
Then, one day,

129
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:03,738
when I woke up,

130
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:08,117
my memories began to return.

131
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:09,869
Little by little.

132
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:12,371
[clears throat] About Cuchy…

133
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:16,042
I adopted her.

134
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:18,544
I took care of her.

135
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:23,466
But she disappeared all of a sudden.

136
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:25,635
But don't worry,

137
00:06:26,385 --> 00:06:27,762
I'll find her soon.

138
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:31,307
That's a promise, bro. Alright?

139
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,017
"Cuchy"?

140
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:34,727
Yeah.

141
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:37,230
Who is this "Cuchy"?

142
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:40,817
[chuckles softly]

143
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,901
Never mind.

144
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:46,948
You really do have a lot
of things you don't remember.

145
00:06:47,031 --> 00:06:49,909
They'll come back. Don't worry.
It's going to be alright, bro.

146
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,872
Anyway, I still have something
to take care of.

147
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:56,332
Sure thing.

148
00:06:58,292 --> 00:06:59,544
[in English] Good to see you, Felix.

149
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:04,215
[Felix scoffs lightly]

150
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,009
When you're back at the NLEA,

151
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:09,303
keep quiet about what you know.

152
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:11,848
Especially around Felix.

153
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:14,851
Don't worry, Sir Marcus.

154
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,978
I'll keep a low profile,

155
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:19,856
so I can be your eyes from within.

156
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:25,903
[Harold] <i>If you really are</i>
<i>the traitor among us,</i>

157
00:07:27,029 --> 00:07:31,659
<i>does that mean you killed</i>
<i>Russel, Patrick, and Oliver?</i>

158
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:36,581
<i>If so, I'll make sure you pay.</i>

159
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:38,708
[dramatic sting]

160
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,918
[traffic noise]

161
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:43,629
- [woman 1] They're coming.
- [woman 2] Yes.

162
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:44,797
[Zubina] They're here.

163
00:07:46,007 --> 00:07:46,883
[gearshift clicks]

164
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:52,722
[Omar] There they are.

165
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,348
‪[car doors clicking shut]

166
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:55,475
[Omar] Jamilah…

167
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,351
Uh, you have nothing
to worry about, Doctor.

168
00:07:57,435 --> 00:07:59,645
We've got your back. We'll protect you.

169
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:00,855
Come on, let's go.

170
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:04,484
Doctor, as long as you're
in our community, you're safe.

171
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:06,027
- Let's go.
- Follow us.

172
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:07,695
- [Teresa] Thank you very much.
- [Zubina] Stay alert, everyone.

173
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:10,448
Keep your eyes open.

174
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:13,326
[suspenseful music playing]

175
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:17,663
[Norhana] Take a left turn.

176
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:24,337
Sir Mustapha's investigation
was nearly complete.

177
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:26,047
[thrilling music playing]

178
00:08:26,130 --> 00:08:27,882
He was about to prove

179
00:08:27,965 --> 00:08:31,177
that it was General Carillo
behind the destabilization

180
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:33,971
and reveal his connection
to Madrigal, Solares,

181
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:38,309
and other high-ranking corrupt officials
within the NLEA and SID.

182
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:41,145
- [Jalil] That's why he was killed.
- [sighs]

183
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:42,813
- Our problem at the moment
- [slams table]

184
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:46,275
is that we still don't have
any solid evidence against Carillo.

185
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:47,818
We know who the enemy is,

186
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:50,488
we know who his accomplices are, but…

187
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:53,574
how are we going to prove that?

188
00:08:56,118 --> 00:08:57,620
- What's wrong?
- [scoffs]

189
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:02,291
I still can't quite believe it.

190
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:05,044
I've gotten used to knowing you as Espina.

191
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:06,420
As a colleague.

192
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,631
As a mission partner.

193
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,174
As a friend.

194
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:14,470
But not as… a brother.

195
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:17,807
[melodramatic music playing]

196
00:09:20,309 --> 00:09:21,227
[emotional music playing]

197
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:22,395
Me too.

198
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:26,732
I still can't quite grasp…

199
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:31,279
the fact that I have another family
besides my father and Jamilah.

200
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:38,494
The truth is,
I haven't regained all my memories yet.

201
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:44,000
All I can recall
are my final moments with you and…

202
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,295
Mama.

203
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:51,132
And it's clear to me now
where I came from.

204
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:53,259
[exhales deeply]

205
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:04,103
- How?
- I found this where you were taken.

206
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:08,232
I was planning to return it,
but then out of nowhere…

207
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:11,360
some of my memories started flooding back.

208
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:13,446
What do you remember?

209
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,992
I-I remember…

210
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:21,329
every time this broke,
you would fix it for me.

211
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:24,582
- I fixed it.
- Yay!

212
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:26,125
My idol!

213
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:28,502
You're so amazing, big bro!

214
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:30,338
[young Gabriel] <i>I love you!</i>

215
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:33,132
[young Marcus] <i>I love you too, Gabriel.</i>

216
00:10:33,215 --> 00:10:34,884
[chuckles] Even though
you always found me annoying.

217
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,135
[chuckles lightly]

218
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,513
You really loved me that much.

219
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:42,099
You remembered how annoying you were?

220
00:10:44,393 --> 00:10:47,021
That's good.
What you remembered was accurate.

221
00:10:47,688 --> 00:10:48,689
[chuckles softly]

222
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:50,441
[Jalil] Here you go.

223
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,735
I'm returning it to you.

224
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,533
This belongs to you.

225
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:02,828
I'm glad that…

226
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,624
it'll finally return to its true owner.

227
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:11,379
- Take it, bro.
- [sniffles]

228
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:18,761
That's why, uh…

229
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:22,431
I could feel a connection
to Doctor Teresa,

230
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:24,225
even when we were still
at each other's throat.

231
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:28,396
It's only now that I understand why…

232
00:11:29,271 --> 00:11:30,648
why I was feeling that way.

233
00:11:33,401 --> 00:11:35,027
Because we're siblings.

234
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:36,404
Because you're my… [voice breaks]

235
00:11:37,696 --> 00:11:39,448
Because you're my brother.
[sniffles lightly]

236
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:43,327
Bro…

237
00:11:44,995 --> 00:11:48,374
When this is all over,
we'll have so much to catch up on

238
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:51,627
and discover about each other.

239
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:59,218
But for now, we need
to take down General Carillo.

240
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:01,971
And also Felix.

241
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:03,806
[music turns tense]

242
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:05,433
He killed my father.

243
00:12:06,016 --> 00:12:07,893
- A lot of people have died.
- [Jalil sniffles]

244
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:10,104
Many have gotten involved.

245
00:12:10,187 --> 00:12:12,064
And many more could be.

246
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:14,024
All of our colleagues…

247
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:17,403
I'm sure General Carillo
will come after them too.

248
00:12:19,363 --> 00:12:21,657
We have to take him down now.

249
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:24,535
The sooner the better.

250
00:12:24,618 --> 00:12:26,662
[music fades]

251
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:32,501
[intriguing music playing]

252
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:37,840
Ma'am?

253
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:39,633
Please don't get it out. I'm begging you.

254
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,177
But, Edrick, if I don't--

255
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,304
If you're not scared for your life,

256
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:46,390
just please, please,
at least be scared for my life.

257
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:48,309
[in English] Just think about it.

258
00:12:49,226 --> 00:12:52,104
It is our responsibility
to expose the evidence

259
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:53,731
left by Datu Rahman.

260
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:58,569
Especially now that his son,
Jalil, is in danger

261
00:12:58,652 --> 00:13:00,237
because of General Carillo.

262
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:01,780
[Edrick] But, ma'am!

263
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:04,825
This will give justice to Datu Rahman,

264
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:08,120
to all those who were massacred
on the island of Damai,

265
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:10,039
to Ahmad Mustapha,

266
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:12,416
and to all of their victims.

267
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,553
- Sir!
- Sir Azuelo!

268
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:26,555
Why? What happened?

269
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:29,517
- Sir, General Ocampo has been released.
- What?

270
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,852
Even Major Yulo and Captain Valdez, sir.

271
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:34,522
And Colonel del Mundo's men.

272
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:36,607
[in English] Goddammit!

273
00:13:42,363 --> 00:13:44,114
Sir, General Villanueva.

274
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:48,661
With all due respect,

275
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:50,829
what does this mean, sir?

276
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:53,082
The court order has been issued.

277
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:56,877
Their arrests were not valid.

278
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:59,213
Because the officer who arrested them,

279
00:13:59,838 --> 00:14:01,382
who is Major Espina,

280
00:14:01,465 --> 00:14:03,217
isn't a real cop.

281
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:07,471
- [music intensifies]
- [dramatic stinging]

282
00:14:12,101 --> 00:14:14,562
And it turns out
all of the evidence against them

283
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:18,023
was fabricated by Agent Reyes and Espina.

284
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:20,025
Or should I say,

285
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:22,111
Jalil Abubakar.

286
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:24,113
Or whoever sanctimonious man that is.

287
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:27,449
- Sir.
- [Villanueva] General Ocampo.

288
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:35,040
[in English] Sir, I'm very sorry
for this mess.

289
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,668
No problem, General Villanueva.

290
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:41,547
[music turns tense]

291
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:47,511
[whispers] We're not yet through.

292
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:53,517
[tense music playing]

293
00:15:05,988 --> 00:15:08,115
[in English] And one more thing, Emil.

294
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:12,745
- [in English] You are hereby fired
- [men] What?

295
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:15,789
as the director
of the Special Investigations Division!

296
00:15:15,873 --> 00:15:16,957
[Ryan] What?

297
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:19,793
And you will be placed under investigation

298
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:23,380
for conspiring with Agent Reyes
and Jalil Abubakar!

299
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:29,595
Effective immediately, Task Force Alpha

300
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:32,389
is hereby dissolved!

301
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:34,642
- Sir!
- We didn't do anything wrong!

302
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,685
- You can't just do this to us--
- [Villanueva, in English] Silence!

303
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:40,105
You should be grateful!
This is me being kind to you!

304
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:43,734
I could've dismissed you from service!

305
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,962
[tires screech]

306
00:16:06,006 --> 00:16:08,092
[suspenseful music playing]

307
00:16:09,593 --> 00:16:10,761
- [Usman] Hey!
- [Zubina, Norhana] Hey! Hey!

308
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:12,221
- Hey! Hey!
- Hey! Hey!

309
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:13,389
- Hey!
- Hold on! Hold on!

310
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:15,516
- Why are you here?
- [Zubina] Stop him! Stop him!

311
00:16:15,599 --> 00:16:17,351
- Why are you here?
- Who are you?

312
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:19,311
[Norhana] Hey, hey, hey, you, you.

313
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:21,730
You're up to something bad, aren't you?
Why are you here?

314
00:16:22,731 --> 00:16:24,066
Start talking!

315
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:28,362
When I'm not here, you're looking for me.

316
00:16:28,445 --> 00:16:30,781
Now I'm here, and you're asking why.

317
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:32,658
Who are you anyway?

318
00:16:32,741 --> 00:16:33,784
I'll beat him up.

319
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,244
- Hold on, hold on.
- Rashid, Rashid.

320
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:37,997
I'm sorry, ma'am and sir.

321
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,916
I'm just looking for Jamilah Abubakar.
I'd like to talk to her.

322
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,001
- Is she here?
- What's this?

323
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:43,127
- Jamilah?
- Jamilah.

324
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,878
- Hold on.
- [Norhana] Jamilah.

325
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:47,297
Aren't you Miss Maya Mae's cameraman?

326
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,383
Yes, that's me.

327
00:16:49,466 --> 00:16:51,927
[indistinct chattering]

328
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:53,637
Why are you looking for me?

329
00:16:54,304 --> 00:16:56,932
Where can we possibly get evidence

330
00:16:57,474 --> 00:16:59,643
against Carillo?

331
00:16:59,727 --> 00:17:03,022
[phone vibrating]

332
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:07,568
Jamilah. Why? What's wrong?

333
00:17:07,651 --> 00:17:10,779
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil, Sir Marcus,</i>
<i>Edrick has something to tell you.</i>

334
00:17:14,074 --> 00:17:16,702
[Edrick] <i>Sir Marcus.</i>
<i>Sir, I need your help.</i>

335
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:18,912
Ms. MMK and I could get in trouble.

336
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:19,955
[people gasp]

337
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,291
Why, Edrick? What's wrong?

338
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:24,501
Before the live interview,

339
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:27,713
Datu Rahman gave an envelope to Ms. MMK.

340
00:17:29,256 --> 00:17:30,924
What envelope? What's on it?

341
00:17:32,217 --> 00:17:34,261
Substantial evidence, sir…

342
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:36,722
against General Carillo.

343
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:37,681
[Zubina] Really?

344
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,934
[Edrick] <i>Datu Rahman said</i>
<i>it was given to him</i>

345
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:42,394
<i>by General Guerzon.</i>

346
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,688
Ms. MMK is being stubborn.

347
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,398
She really wants to get it out.

348
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,108
I told her to drop it.

349
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:50,652
But she's determined to do it.

350
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:52,029
She'll expose everything.

351
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:53,739
Where's the envelope right now?

352
00:17:53,822 --> 00:17:55,240
She has it, sir.

353
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,826
She doesn't even want it out of her sight.

354
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:00,996
[Edrick] <i>Sir Marcus. Sir.</i>

355
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,290
She won't listen to me.

356
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:06,585
[Edrick] <i>I have no one else</i>
<i>to call but you.</i>

357
00:18:06,668 --> 00:18:07,795
[in English] Sir…

358
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:10,881
save Miss Maya Mae.

359
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:14,134
[sobs, in English] Save the country!

360
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:18,722
[Jalil breathes sharply]

361
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:20,099
[Marcus grunts] Shit! Argh!

362
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:25,479
[heavy breathing]

363
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:32,194
Uncle Omar!

364
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:33,445
Doctor!

365
00:18:34,154 --> 00:18:36,657
[Rashid knocks on door] Uncle Omar!
Uncle Omar!

366
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:41,161
[Rashid knocks on door] Uncle Omar!
Uncle Omar.

367
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:43,038
- Yes?
- Miss Maya Mae has a new episode.

368
00:18:43,122 --> 00:18:44,748
- She does? Come in.
- [Norhana] Ha?

369
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,709
[in English] Okay, everyone.
Quiet on the set!

370
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,044
[in English] Ready…

371
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:52,965
[in English] In three, two, one and…

372
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:55,592
With the growing questions

373
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:58,512
about the continued increase
in gun-related violence

374
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:00,681
and alleged destabilization plot,

375
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:04,977
who would've thought
that the answers we are searching for

376
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:06,562
are just here?

377
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:09,189
[in English] Inside
this ordinary-looking envelope.

378
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:13,944
Together, let's find out
what evidence it holds

379
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:16,530
and whose names it involves.

380
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:21,326
[in English] This is Maya Mae Kalaw,
<i>Inside The Truth,</i> live.

381
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:25,747
[suspenseful music playing]

382
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:47,186
[in English] This envelope
that I'm holding right here

383
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:51,732
contains very sensitive
and very incriminating information.

384
00:19:51,815 --> 00:19:53,233
[in English] So much so--

385
00:19:53,317 --> 00:19:55,861
[gunshots blasting]

386
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:58,322
[pensive music playing]

387
00:19:58,405 --> 00:20:00,616
- They're under attack.
- Oh God.

388
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:02,284
[inaudible]

389
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:04,161
- What's that?
- What happened?

390
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:06,246
What's going on?

391
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:07,331
[gunshots blasting]

392
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,708
- What's going on?
- Let's hurry up.

393
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:11,585
Guys, let's get on with this.

394
00:20:11,668 --> 00:20:13,253
[in English] Miss Maya,
are we going to do this?

395
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:15,255
- [in English] Let's do this.
- [in English] Can we do this again-- Okay.

396
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:17,966
[in English] Okay, okay, everyone!
Continue rolling…

397
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:18,926
- [in English] In three,
- [gunshots blasting]

398
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:20,761
- [staff screaming]
- two, one!

399
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:25,015
These documents Datu Rahman gave me

400
00:20:25,098 --> 00:20:26,725
when we did our live tell-all interview--

401
00:20:26,808 --> 00:20:27,851
- [gunshots blasting]
- [staff screaming]

402
00:20:27,935 --> 00:20:29,728
[gunshots blasting]

403
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:32,814
[staff screaming]

404
00:20:36,985 --> 00:20:39,363
These contain complete bank documents,

405
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:42,032
from when money was deposited
to when it's withdrawn.

406
00:20:42,115 --> 00:20:45,410
[Maya Mae] <i>Included as well</i>
<i>are waybills and shipping documents.</i>

407
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:49,790
There is also a list of the weapons
missing from our armory,

408
00:20:49,873 --> 00:20:51,500
- from our police force…
- [gunshots blasting]

409
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:52,626
[screaming]

410
00:20:53,210 --> 00:20:54,544
…and from our armed forces.

411
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:59,049
These are high-powered guns
that were later sold in the black market.

412
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:00,634
- [gunshots blasting]
- [staff screaming]

413
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:02,886
- Stop this!
- Stop this!

414
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:04,805
- [gunshots]
- [staff screaming]

415
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:07,933
[staff screaming, crying]

416
00:21:13,188 --> 00:21:15,565
- [grunting]
- [gunshots blasting]

417
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:19,903
And because these documents
will reveal everything,

418
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:24,074
it's no wonder the culprit
is willing to kill to get these.

419
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:25,075
[screaming]

420
00:21:25,158 --> 00:21:27,077
[staff screaming]

421
00:21:29,413 --> 00:21:30,372
[Maya Mae groans]

422
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:31,581
- [kick lands]
- [goon groans]

423
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:33,875
[Marcus grunting]

424
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:35,377
[goon grunts]

425
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,045
[both grunting]

426
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:39,715
[Maya Mae grunts]

427
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:44,469
[Jalil grunting]

428
00:21:44,553 --> 00:21:46,346
[goon grunts]

429
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:47,639
[goon groans]

430
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:49,433
[goon groans]

431
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:53,437
[goon grunts]

432
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,397
[Edrick] We have to continue.
Let's continue.

433
00:21:56,857 --> 00:21:57,983
[goon grunts]

434
00:21:58,066 --> 00:22:02,070
Fortunately, Marcus Reyes
and Jalil Abubakar saved us,

435
00:22:02,154 --> 00:22:05,115
who, ironically, are considered
enemies of the State,

436
00:22:05,198 --> 00:22:08,076
but right before your very faces

437
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,870
saved the truth for our country.

438
00:22:11,246 --> 00:22:14,082
So, Marcus Reyes and Jalil Abubakar…

439
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:18,003
This is what I want to tell you.

440
00:22:19,463 --> 00:22:21,548
Thank you very, very much.

441
00:22:22,591 --> 00:22:26,636
[suspenseful music continues]

442
00:22:29,514 --> 00:22:32,350
And when we did
our preliminary investigation,

443
00:22:32,434 --> 00:22:35,645
we saw a lot of familiar names
in this document.

444
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:39,441
<i>Some names appeared many times.</i>

445
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:42,069
But the most frequent one of all

446
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:47,199
was the name of retired
police general Manuel Carillo.

447
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:52,746
[music becomes dramatic]

448
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:32,953
[inaudible]

449
00:23:40,293 --> 00:23:43,797
[thrilling music playing]

450
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:46,550
We almost secured the document, General,

451
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:49,052
but Reyes and Jalil suddenly showed up.

452
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:51,388
They managed to stop us
and took the envelope.

453
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:53,890
- [screams]
- [grunts]

454
00:23:53,974 --> 00:23:56,226
You imbeciles!

455
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:58,145
You good-for-nothing fools!

456
00:23:58,728 --> 00:23:59,771
Raquel!

457
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:02,190
General.

458
00:24:02,274 --> 00:24:03,900
Call everyone!

459
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:10,532
I won't let that damned Marcus
and Jalil bring me down!

460
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:15,537
[stirring music playing]

461
00:24:17,789 --> 00:24:19,374
My sons…

462
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:25,964
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

463
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:34,139
[sighs triumphantly]

464
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:38,602
♪ <i>Opening my eyes after a blink</i> ♪

465
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:47,110
♪ <i>The throne a tyrant playing king…</i> ♪

466
00:24:50,572 --> 00:24:51,781
[grunts]

467
00:24:55,744 --> 00:24:57,662
♪ <i>Everything has an end</i> ♪

468
00:24:57,746 --> 00:25:01,958
♪ <i>If the law is only for a select few</i> ♪

469
00:25:03,251 --> 00:25:07,047
♪ <i>And justice comes with a price</i> ♪

470
00:25:07,130 --> 00:25:10,091
<i>♪ I will not remain silent anymore</i>
<i>This has to stop… ♪</i>

471
00:25:10,175 --> 00:25:14,304
- [screaming in anger]
- [glass shatters]

472
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:17,098
♪ <i>I won't back down</i>
<i>I will fight</i> ♪

473
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:20,602
[breathing heavily]

474
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:25,398
♪ <i>The situation is much worse now</i> ♪

475
00:25:25,482 --> 00:25:29,069
♪ <i>My own blood became my enemy there</i> ♪

476
00:25:29,152 --> 00:25:33,114
[Villanueva] Everything you say
may be used against you

477
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:35,492
in any court in the Philippines.

478
00:25:36,117 --> 00:25:38,328
Do you understand your rights?

479
00:25:40,747 --> 00:25:41,748
Go.

480
00:25:41,831 --> 00:25:44,793
[stirring music playing]

481
00:25:49,172 --> 00:25:50,548
- [reporter 1] General Carillo.
- [camera shutters clicking]

482
00:25:50,632 --> 00:25:53,510
Is it true that you were behind
the destabilization plot

483
00:25:53,593 --> 00:25:54,803
against the administration?

484
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:57,931
[reporter 2] Is it true you want
to overthrow the government?

485
00:25:58,014 --> 00:26:00,976
What's your message
for Marcus Reyes and Jalil Abubakar?

486
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:04,646
- General, your comment, please!
- Tell us your side, sir!

487
00:26:04,729 --> 00:26:06,648
[reporter 2] Do you really plan
to overthrow the government?

488
00:26:06,731 --> 00:26:08,566
- Just a few words, sir!
- What can you say, General?

489
00:26:10,485 --> 00:26:13,738
[music intensifies]

490
00:26:17,492 --> 00:26:20,495
Retired police general
Manuel Carillo was arrested

491
00:26:20,578 --> 00:26:22,497
pursuant to a warrant of arrest

492
00:26:22,580 --> 00:26:27,210
issued by Judge Kayla Vonzel
of Nilad Regional Trial Court.

493
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:30,505
<i>This was after Maya Mae Kalaw</i>
<i>made an exposé,</i>

494
00:26:30,588 --> 00:26:33,383
<i>linking General Carillo</i>

495
00:26:33,967 --> 00:26:36,928
<i>to a gun-smuggling syndicate</i>

496
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:39,389
<i>and an alleged plot to overthrow</i>
<i>the government.</i>

497
00:26:39,472 --> 00:26:42,309
[music intensifies]

498
00:26:53,486 --> 00:26:55,697
His actions are very suspicious.

499
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:56,656
What do you mean, sir?

500
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:59,409
[Teresa] <i>I'm so relieved</i>
<i>that you are safe, my sons!</i>

501
00:26:59,492 --> 00:27:02,329
[in English] I trusted you,
but you played me for a fool!

502
00:27:02,412 --> 00:27:03,621
You're too weak.

503
00:27:03,705 --> 00:27:07,125
[Manuel] <i>You have to trust me.</i>

504
00:27:07,208 --> 00:27:10,754
[Jalil] How do we find
Carillo's remaining accomplices?

505
00:27:11,463 --> 00:27:14,299
- That's Carillo's next target.
- [gunshots, clamoring]

506
00:27:14,382 --> 00:27:16,009
[Natalia] <i>Who's behind all this?</i>

507
00:27:16,634 --> 00:27:18,261
[Maya Mae, in English]
<i>Go find the president.</i>

508
00:27:19,429 --> 00:27:22,557
[Carillo] <i>The Philippines</i>
<i>is about to lose its president.</i>

509
00:27:23,141 --> 00:27:24,893
[laughs]

510
00:27:24,976 --> 00:27:28,605
[suspenseful music playing]
